The Hash Slinging Snacker BOT 04/14/2023 5:42 PM
Hello and welcome to your confessional channel! This is where you should dump all your thoughts about the game or anything else you want to talk about. You may also receive questions from hosts and spectators alike throughout the season. Please answer those promptly and have fun with them as well. This is a place you should be using to explain your thoughts on the game and reactions to the events unfolding around you. We want to see your journey progress throughout the season. Only our Hungry Spectators can see this as the season goes, they are all verified and trusted people, so no need to worry about any sort of leaks. Please make the most of your confessionals as it adds to the fun of the game! Spectators love reading these so use them as frequently as you would like. Do not complete challenges, submit votes, use commands, or say anything in here you wouldn't want the other players to see after the season, as this will all be public. To start you off good on these confessionals, please answer these basic starter questions! 1 - Tell us about yourself and your life! 2 - What are your first reactions about the game that lies ahead? 3 - How do you plan on playing this season to become the sole survivor? Good luck and have fun!

GOOD LUCK IM ROOTING FOR YOU
Etay (i am a snack) 04/14/2023 8:46 PM
Hello to all the hungry specs! (And regular specs once the season is finished). I am Etay (not my real name), an 18 year old high school senior who likes to cook, both in the kitchen where I sometimes make myself meals, and in a group chat I have called "The Kitchen" where I make competitive pokemon teams, turning some of the most random seeming mons into actual threats. My initial reaction to the game that lies ahead is that I will have to play very carefully early on; with only 5 people per starting tribe, there is very little room to hide. As for my plan to be the sole survivor this season, I think the key is going to be a strong early social performance, but not so strong that I get targeted in the early merge as a social threat. I believe I will be fairly strong at challenges, so I can try to go for a strategy of using stronger social players who are weaker at challenges as allies and shields. Overall though, I think I just need to make sure that I don't overthink these earlier rounds, or else I might play myself out of the game. Something important that I have learned, however, is that talking to people is key. If people look like they aren't talking much, that's because they aren't talking with you much, and that goes both ways (i.e. if I don't talk much with someone, then they'll think I'm against them and try to get me out). Anyway imma finish this message here before it breaks the character limit. And with that, I welcome you all to my confessionals this season!

@nicucumber roll This one is pretty tough, but after considering my options, I think I have to go with potato chips (either thick ones or barbecue flavored, since those ones are based like me). Just like a bag of potato chips has many chips, I come up with many ideas, some better, some worse, sometimes leaving people salty. And, also like a bag of potato chips, some of my ideas are pure gas. But what makes me the most like potato chips is the fact that if someone were to eat me, I would be crunchy and also not very good for that person's health.

Etay (i am a snack) 04/15/2023 12:12 AM
